_meta.description: Canonical wood species reference — physical, thermal, machining, and lutherie properties. Single source of truth. Species are classified by guitar_relevance: primary (traditional tonewoods), established (well-known guitar woods), emerging (gaining popularity), exploratory (valid woods, not yet common in guitars).

fpl.title: USDA FPL Wood Handbook: Wood as an Engineering Material
fpl.publication: General Technical Report FPL-GTR-282, Forest Products Laboratory, USDA Forest Service, Madison, WI
fpl.provides: thermal_conductivity (Table 3-11, ±20%), SG, Janka, MOR, MOE, shrinkage for ~30 domestic species

wood_database.title: The Wood Database
wood_database.author: Eric Meier
wood_database.provides: density, MOR, MOE for 465 species; per-species URLs in _source_url fields

cirad.title: CIRAD Wood Collection Index
cirad.provides: Specific gravity cross-validation from 34,395 specimens across 1,831 genera

sources.estimation_methods: Thermal k, SCE, specific heat, and Janka (bulk species) estimated from SG/density regressions per FPL guidance. Machining params derived from hardness scale. All estimates flagged with _note fields. Full methodology in SOURCES.md.

units.modulus_of_rupture_mpa: MPa — static bending strength at 12% MC
units.modulus_of_elasticity_gpa: GPa — static bending stiffness at 12% MC
